description:
What is the 3 angels’ message in Revelation 14 about? The backdrop of the messages of the three angels is the throne room of Heaven where John sees the Lamb surrounded by the redeemed, singing praises to God. In this setting, John raises his eyes and sees three angels flying in the midst of heaven.

The three angels capture the world’s attention with loud voices and startling messages. What is the everlasting Gospel that they preach? Why do they proclaim that judgment has come? Who does Babylon represent today? And how should we understand the dire warning given? 

Walter Veith delves into history and opens the pages of Scripture to unravel the mysteries of the Three Angels’ Messages in this series. Filmed in Iceland, a place which so aptly symbolizes the contrast between light and darkness, Walter Veith reveals an arresting message full of significance and vital importance to everyone living today.
